## Quick start

```bash
# Node 18+ required. No `npm install` — zero dependencies (built-in fetch).
export {{PRIMARY_ENV}}=xxx   # {{ENV_LINK}}

node generate.mjs --prompt "..." --aspect landscape
# -> writes out/landscape.{{EXT}} and prints a JSON result line
```

Preview the request without spending anything (no key needed):

```bash
node generate.mjs --prompt "..." --dry-run
```

## Options

| Flag        | Values                                | Default            |
|-------------|---------------------------------------|--------------------|
| `--prompt`  | text, max 2000 chars (**required**)   | —                  |
| `--aspect`  | `square` \| `landscape` \| `portrait` | `square`           |
| `--out`     | output file path                      | `out/<aspect>.{{EXT}}` |
| `--dry-run` | print request, spend nothing          | off                |

## Usable by any AI runtime

- **Claude Code** — reads `SKILL.md`.
- **Codex / Cursor / any shell agent** — read `AGENTS.md`, run the CLI.
- **Tool-use / hosted LLMs** (Bankr LLM Gateway, Surplus, OpenAI, Claude API) — hand the model
  `tool-schema.json` (`openai` or `anthropic` block); the host runs the CLI on the tool call.

